title: Tassel, 1962-51-44, 17th century
medium:
Medium: linen
Technique: knotted with needle lace
creditline: Bequest of Richard Cranch Greenleaf in memory of his mother, Adeline Emma Greenleaf
description: Flat tassel of linen, needle lace, gros Point de Venise. Single loop atached to leaves and floral blossom, outlines by the cordonnet. Tiny knotted clusters attached to tassel at intervals.

exhibitions.title: Treasures from the Cooper Union Museum
